```python
import pandas as pd

df_sales = pd.DataFrame({
    "order_id": [101,102,103,104,105,106,107,108],
    "customer": ["C1","C2","C1","C3","C2","C4","C3","C1"],
    "product":  ["P1","P2","P3","P2","P1","P3","P1","P2"],
    "qty":      [ 2,  1,  3,  2,  1,  2,  4,  1]
})

df_price = pd.DataFrame({
    "product": ["P1","P2","P3"],
    "unit_price": [120, 80, 150]
})
display(df_sales, df_price)
```

# ÌíÄÏù¥

```python
df2 = pd.merge(df_sales, df_price, how = 'left', on='product')
df2['revenue'] = df2['qty']*df2['unit_price']
df_customer = df2.groupby('customer')['revenue'].agg('sum').reset_index(name = 'total_revenue')
df_customer['revenue_share'] = df_customer['total_revenue']/sum(df_customer['total_revenue'])
top2_customers = df_customer.sort_values(by=['total_revenue', 'customer'], ascending=[False, True])['customer'][:2].to_list()
display(df2, df_customer, top2_customers)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,4))
df_color = df_customer.copy()
df_color['top2_bool'] = df_color['customer'].isin(top2_customers)
df_color['color'] = df_color['top2_bool'].map({True: 'orange', False: 'gray'})
color = df_color['color'].to_list()
ax.bar(df_customer['customer'], df_customer['total_revenue'], color = color)
ax.set_title("Total Revenue by Customer")
ax.set_xlabel("Customer")
ax.set_ylabel("Total Revenue")
ax.grid(False)
ax.tick_params(axis="x", labelrotation=0)
plt.show()
```
